    retrieve or place the model.safetensors for Geneformer (6L?) in cache, zipped

    get_gf_safetensors.Rd

    retrieve or place the model.safetensors for Geneformer (6L?) in cache, zipped

    get_gf_safetensors(cache = BiocFileCache::BiocFileCache())

    Arguments

    cache

    instance of BiocFileCache::BiocFileCache()

    Value

    character path to zip file once cached

    Note

    A README.txt is included in the zip file

    Examples

    pa = get_gf_safetensors()
td = tempdir()
unzip(pa, exdir=td)
nwts_safet(file.path(td, "GF_safetensors", "model.safetensors"))
#> [1] 10290770
st = get_safet() # not standard, hands live python ref
oo = st$safe_open(file.path(td, "GF_safetensors", "model.safetensors"), "pt")
mk = oo$keys()
length(mk)
#> [1] 107
head(sapply(mk, function(z) oo$get_tensor(z)$shape))
#> $bert.embeddings.LayerNorm.bias
#> torch.Size([256])
#> 
#> $bert.embeddings.LayerNorm.weight
#> torch.Size([256])
#> 
#> $bert.embeddings.position_embeddings.weight

#> 
#> $bert.embeddings.position_ids
#> torch.Size([1, 2048])
#>
